'''四天工作制'''是一种工作场所或学校使其雇员或学生每[[星期|星期]]上班或上学四天而非传统的五天的一种安排<ref name="#1">Rex L. Facer II and Lori L. Wadsworth. 2010. “Four-day Workweeks: Current Research and Practice” Connecticut Law Review 42, (4): 1031-1046.</ref>。这种安排既有可能是因为[[弹性工时|弹性工作制]]，亦有可能是为了减少成本。

2008年，[[美国|美国]][[犹他州|犹他州]]州政府公务员开始执行每周星期一至星期四工作四天，每天工作10小时的安排<ref name="#1"/><ref name=Utah>{{cite news |title=Utah is going to a 4-day workweek |agency=Associated Press |date=July 3, 2008 |work=MSNBC |url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/25518225 |accessdate=2012-02-17 |archive-date=2012-01-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120119020741/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/25518225 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。通过政府机构在星期五一天的关闭，犹他州政府期望可以减少在电费、供暖费及公车油费等费用上的运营成本<ref name=Utah/>。许多美国地方政府已执行四天工作制较长时间<ref>Lori L. Wadsworth, Rex L. Facer II, and Chyleen A. Arbon. 2010. “Alternative Work Schedules in Local Government: Qui Bono?” Review of Public Personnel Administration 30, (3): 322-340.</ref><ref>Rex L. Facer II and Lori L. Wadsworth. 2008. “Alternative Work Schedules and Work Family Balance: A Research Note.” Review of Public Personnel Administration 28, (2): 166-177.</ref><ref> Rex L. Facer II, Lori L. Wadsworth, and Chyleen Arbon. 2009. “Cities Leading the Way: The Use of Alternative Work Schedules by Cities. 2009 Municipal Yearbook. ICMA Press: Washington DC, pp. 28-33.</ref>。

[[美国|美国]][[夏威夷州|夏威夷州]]的[[公立学校|公立学校]]在2010年5月17日一天关闭<ref>{{cite news |title=Schools' New Math: The Four-Day Week |first=Chris Herring |date=March 8, 2010 |work=The Wall Street Journal |url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052748704869304575104124088312524.html |accessdate=2012-02-17 |archive-date=2012-03-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120310005119/http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052748704869304575104124088312524.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。美国农村地区超过100个[[学区|学区]]执行每周上四天学的安排。这些学区通常将每天的教学时间延长一小时或更长时间<ref name=rural>{{cite news |title=In rural areas, the four-day school week is growing in popularity |agency=Associated Press |first=Greg |last=Toppo |date=August 20, 2002 |work=The Christian Science Monitor |url=http://www.csmonitor.com/2002/0820/p14s02-lecs.html |accessdate=2012-02-17 |archive-date=2012-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120804214448/http://www.csmonitor.com/2002/0820/p14s02-lecs.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Four-Day School Weeks |work=National Conference of State Legislatures |accessdate=February 3, 2011 |url=http://www.ncsl.org/default.aspx?tabid=12934 |archive-date=2011-07-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707083751/http://www.ncsl.org/default.aspx?tabid=12934 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。四天工作制在学校的实行通常是为了在[[交通|交通]]、供暖及[[代课教师|代课教师]]等方面节省开支<ref name=rural/>。

此外冰島、西班牙、新西蘭也有進行四天工作制實驗<ref>{{cite news |title=冰岛缩短工作时长试验：四天工作制几国欢乐几国忧 |url=http://news.stnn.cc/guoji/2021/0810/888087.shtml |accessdate=2021-08-10 |archive-date=2021-08-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210810143932/http://news.stnn.cc/guoji/2021/0810/888087.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>。冰島的結論是所有參加者身體更加健康、心情更加舒暢、工作效率更高，工作成果反而增加。<ref>{{Cite web|title=每周工作四天是白日夢嗎？工作時間的歷史演變與爭議|url=https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/world-57763180|access-date=2021-11-15|date=2021-07-10|work=BBC News 中文|language=zh-hant|archive-date=2021-11-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211115090405/https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/world-57763180|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 2022年 ==
2月，[[比利時|比利時]][[聯邦政府|聯邦政府]]通過，員工將可以選擇一週工作四日，且下班時間有權忽略來自雇主等工作相關的訊息。<ref>{{cite news | title = Belgium approves four-day week and gives employees the right to ignore their bosses after work | language = en | url = https://www.euronews.com/next/2022/02/15/belgium-approves-four-day-week-and-gives-employees-the-right-to-ignore-their-bosses | work = euronews.com | date = 2022-02-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Belgien führt Vier-Tage-Woche ein | language = de | url = https://www.tagesspiegel.de/wirtschaft/weniger-tage-bei-gleicher-arbeitszeit-belgien-fuehrt-vier-tage-woche-ein/28073230.html | work = Tagesspiegel.de | date = 2022-02-16}}</ref>

6月，[[英國|英國]]70家[[企業|企業]]超過3300名員工，將實施一週工作四日，提出100:80:100工作模式，即以100%的薪資換取80%的工作時數，並一樣達到100%的工作效能<ref>{{cite news | title = Thousands of UK workers begin world’s biggest trial of four-day week | language = en | url = https://www.theguardian.com/business/2022/jun/06/thousands-workers-worlds-biggest-trial-four-day-week | work = The Guardian | date = 2022-06-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Volle Produktivität bei 80 Prozent Arbeit? Die Briten testen die 4-Tage-Woche | language = de | url = https://www.welt.de/wirtschaft/article239210799/Vier-Tage-Woche-Die-Briten-testen-das-100-80-100-Modell.html | work = welt.de | date = 2022-06-07}}</ref>，是目前試辦四日工作制最大規模者<ref>{{cite news | title = Four-day workweek: 3,300 employees in the UK start biggest trial of its kind | language = en | url = https://www.euronews.com/next/2022/06/05/four-day-week-3-000-employees-in-the-uk-to-take-part-in-the-biggest-trial-of-its-kind | work = Euronews.com | date = 2022-06-06}}</ref>。

